Document: AnimationNodeBlendTree
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeblendtree.rst
Summary: A node that allows blending animations using a graph-based interface.

Inherits: AnimationNode < AnimationRootNode < AnimationNode < Resource

The AnimationNodeBlendTree is a node that allows you to blend animations using a graph-based interface. It is a powerful tool for creating complex animation logic, such as state machines, blend spaces, and more.

The blend tree works by connecting various animation nodes (such as AnimationNodeBlend2, AnimationNodeBlend3, AnimationNodeStateMachine, etc.) together in a graph. Each node represents a specific animation or a way to blend animations. The output of the blend tree is a single animation, which can then be used by an AnimationPlayer or another AnimationNode.

You can add nodes to the blend tree by right-clicking on the graph background and selecting "Add Node". You can then connect the output of one node to the input of another by dragging a connection from the output port of the source node to the input port of the destination node.

The blend tree also allows you to define parameters that can be controlled externally. These parameters can be used to drive the blending logic, such as controlling the blend amount between two animations or selecting a specific animation from a state machine. You can add parameters by clicking the "Add Parameter" button in the inspector.

The AnimationNodeBlendTree is a fundamental building block for advanced animation systems in Godot. It provides a visual and intuitive way to manage and control complex animation sequences.
